---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Pleaz Dashboard">
  <section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Title + intro -->
      <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="mb-2">Pleaz Power BI Dashboards</h1>
        <p class="text-muted">
          While working at Pleaz, I developed a series of Power BI dashboards that enabled teams across the organization to track key metrics.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Role / Methods -->
      <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
          <h2 class="h5">Overview & My Role</h2>
          <p class="mb-2">
            I created PowerBI dashboards that visualized business and product metrics tailored to the needs of different teams. 
            This involved working closely with stakeholders to define questions, shaping KPIs, and iterating on clear, accessible visualizations.         
          </p>
          <ul class="mb-0">
            <li><strong>My role:</strong> requirements gathering, data modeling, dashboard design, roll-out & support</li>
            <li><strong>Impact:</strong> clearer view of adoption and usage patterns, faster identification of at-risk accounts, and better prioritization for content</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
          <h2 class="h5">Methods & Tools</h2>
          <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Power BI (data model, DAX, visuals)</li>
            <li>SQL/ETL for data preparation</li>
            <li>Stakeholder workshops to define KPIs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Example 1 -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Product Usage Dashboard (Management, Content & Customer Success)</h3>
        <p>
          Designed for management, content, and customer success teams, this dashboard tracked weekly activations and customer usage. 
          It helped leadership monitor adoption trends, enabled customer success to focus their outreach, and gave the content team insights 
          into which types of videos were most watched.
        </p>
        <img
          src="/assets/pleaz-dashboard/pleaz_dashboard_002.jpg"
          alt="Overview dashboard for weekly activations and usage by customer"
          class="img-fluid project-shot mt-3"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Example 2 -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Routine Dashboard (Customer Success)</h3>
        <p>
          Helping customers establish a routine was the top priority for the Customer Success team. 
          This dashboard showed time-of-day usage patterns, giving them a daily tool to track when clients engaged with the 
          platform and guide them toward building stronger routines. 
        </p>
        <img
          src="/assets/pleaz-dashboard/pleaz_dashboard_003.jpg"
          alt="Routine dashboard showing time-of-day usage patterns"
          class="img-fluid project-shot mt-3"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Example 3 -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="h5 mb-3">New Product Adoption (Management, Product & Customer Success)</h3>
        <p>
          Built to monitor the rollout of a new product, this dashboard tracked weekly active users and adoption at the team level. 
          It gave management visibility on performance, helped customer success and sales teams identify engaged accounts, 
          and supported the product team as they iterated on the launch. 
        </p>
        <img
          src="/assets/pleaz-dashboard/pleaz_dashboard_005.png"
          alt="New product adoption dashboard with weekly active users and team breakdowns"
          class="img-fluid project-shot mt-3"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- PDF link -->
      <div class="text-center mt-5">
        <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="/assets/pleaz-dashboard/pleaz_dashboard_anonymiseret.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          View full dashboard (PDF)
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

